Baltimore, Philadelphia, Washington, D.C.

194
00:13:18,740 --> 00:13:21,580
特勤局的标准警戒线…
Standard Secret Service protective cordon

195
00:13:21,880 --> 00:13:24,510
通常设在八百八十码之外
is out to 880 yards.

196
00:13:24,620 --> 00:13:29,280
但截获的情报称，这次 袭击地点会定在1英里之外
But this intercept claims that the shot will be taken from beyond a mile.

197
00:13:29,390 --> 00:13:32,380
你去实地勘查一下 然后告诉我们你的做法
We need you to scout, tell us how you would do it,

198
00:13:32,760 --> 00:13:34,250
我们就会阻止他
so we could stop it.

199
00:13:35,230 --> 00:13:39,750
不过老实说，我不大相信 这样的袭击会得逞
I'm not entirely convinced that a shot like this could be made.

200
00:13:41,070 --> 00:13:43,260
但不能掉以轻心
But let's not take the chance.

201
00:13:44,500 --> 00:13:46,700
你的远距离射击能力到底怎样？
Your longer shots were never confirmed.

202
00:13:46,800 --> 00:13:48,700
远距离射击通常发生在…
That's because long shots generally go places

203
00:13:48,810 --> 00:13:51,640
你们不愿意去确认的场合
you wouldn't wanna have to go afterwards to confirm them.

204
00:13:51,740 --> 00:13:54,340
确认只是做表面文章而已
Confirmation's a desk pogue's problem.

205
00:13:55,180 --> 00:13:57,440
知道远距离射击要考虑什么吗？
You know what it takes to make a shot at that range?

206
00:13:57,550 --> 00:13:59,070
需要考虑所有相关的因素：
Everything comes into play that far.

207
00:13:59,180 --> 00:14:02,280
湿度、温度、高度、 风向、扬尘…
Humidity, elevation, temperature, wind, spindrift.

208
00:14:02,390 --> 00:14:03,720
子弹飞向目标需要六到十秒时间
There's a 6- to10-second flight time

209
00:14:03,820 --> 00:14:05,910
所以必须估算提前量
so you have to shoot at where the target's going to be.

210
00:14:05,880 --> 00:14:08,970
甚至科里奥利作用*和地球自转都得考虑 *对旋转体系中进行直线运动的质点由于惯性产生偏移的一种描述

211
00:14:06,020 --> 00:14:09,110
Even the Coriolis effect, the spin of the Earth, comes into play.

212
00:14:09,230 --> 00:14:11,460
总统会穿防弹衣，所以要射击头部
President'll be wearing body amour. That means a headshot,

213
00:14:11,560 --> 00:14:12,720
还要在一英里之外
at over a mile.

214
00:14:12,830 --> 00:14:15,090
你相信真有这么大本事的枪手吗？
You believe there's a shooter involved capable of making this shot?

215
00:14:15,200 --> 00:14:16,430
我相信
Yes.

216
00:14:16,530 --> 00:14:18,900
那麻烦可就大了 你们一定要找到枪手
Well, then you got a real problem. You need to find the shooter.

217
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:21,370
那是另一批人的任务
That's being worked on from another direction.

218
00:14:21,570 --> 00:14:23,230
我们需要你干这事
We need you to do this.

219
00:14:23,340 --> 00:14:25,310
我根本不喜欢现任总统
Don't really like the President much.

220
00:14:25,410 --> 00:14:27,310
前任总统更不喜欢
Didn't like the one before that much, either.

221
00:14:27,410 --> 00:14:29,280
但是你喜欢总统制吗？
You like the idea of the President?

222
00:14:29,650 --> 00:14:31,110
喜欢自由的国家吗？
Living in a free country?

223
00:14:31,220 --> 00:14:33,650
难道我们能容忍让坏人统治吗…
Do we allow America to be ruled by thugs?

224
00:14:33,750 --> 00:14:35,510
没关系，几年而已
Sure, some years we do.

225
00:14:36,750 --> 00:14:39,620
我相信你曾站在国旗前…
I believe you stood before a flag

226
00:14:40,120 --> 00:14:41,390
庄严宣誓过…
and solemnly swore

227
00:14:42,290 --> 00:14:46,160
要支持和捍卫美国宪法…
that you'd support and defend the Constitution of the United States

228
00:14:46,260 --> 00:14:47,920
抗击一切敌人
against all enemies,

229
00:14:48,030 --> 00:14:49,660
无论来自国内外
foreign and domestic.

230
00:14:49,770 --> 00:14:51,700
五分钟到了
I think your five minutes is up.

231
00:15:01,180 --> 00:15:02,700
听着，孩子
Listen to me, son.

232
00:15:04,780 --> 00:15:06,910
我不希望你下星期打开电视
I don't want you to turn on the TV next week

233
00:15:08,120 --> 00:15:10,420
看到总统身亡时…
and see the President dead,

234
00:15:10,520 --> 00:15:13,180
后悔自己没阻止这一切
and know you could've done something about it.

235
00:15:14,020 --> 00:15:16,050
希望你好自为之
Don't do that to yourself.

236
00:15:36,850 --> 00:15:38,640
这是新型号吗？
Is that the new one?

237
00:15:38,750 --> 00:15:40,010
那辆车
The truck.

238
00:15:41,520 --> 00:15:42,990
装有大马力发动机？
You got the big engine in there?

239
00:15:43,090 --> 00:15:46,650
我看看，八升 V-8 发动机
Wow, look at that, huh? Eight-liter V8.

240
00:15:46,760 --> 00:15:50,450
厉害，环保署竟然 不管你的每公里油耗
Thing's so big, EPA doesn't even bother to give you the gas mileage for it.

241
00:15:50,560 --> 00:15:52,120
